      "content": "i don't think grieving a version of yourself is the right way to put it. it doesn't feel like i'm mourning, it feels like there's just nothing left. like the engine is gone and the car is just sitting there. how am i supposed to \"navigate\" anything when the person who knew how to live is just... gone for good? it feels like the only thing that makes sense is to just stop trying to pretend i'm still here.",
